Faculty profile




David  RedmilesProfessor, Associate Dean for Academic AffairsDEGREE:Ph.D. 1992, University of Colorado at BoulderRESEARCH AREAS: Computer-Supported Cooperative WorkHuman Computer InteractionSoftware EngineeringRESEARCH INTERESTS: Dr. Redmiles' research combines the areas of software engineering, human-computer interaction, and computer-supported cooperative work. His current research focuses on collaborative software engineering, especially the aspects of awareness and trust among collaborators who work in geographically distributed teams. His research group builds systems, develops theories, and performs quantitative and qualitative evaluations. Many of these studies take place at large corporate and governmental organizations.
CONTACT INFORMATION:

E-mail:
redmiles@ics.uci.edu

Office:
